TASK 7
Your goal is to use two ATmega328P Arduinos to demonstrate basic SPI
communication at the register level. One Arduino must act as the Master and
the other as the Slave. The Master must send a single decimal value (0–255)
once every second through SPI, and the Slave must correctly receive that value
and display it on the Serial Monitor. You must configure all SPI settings using
the SPCR, SPSR, SPDR, DDRB, and PORTB registers only.
The Master must transmit a sequence of three specific decimal values every
second in the following order:
85 → 170 → 255
repeat

